<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-065-317 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 235 935</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 2 1991 v13 n35 p40(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wellfleet adds to WAN routing; extended source routing enhancesToken Ring LANs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Coursey, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Wellfleet Communications has developed a new technique for dealingwith routing constraints on IBM Token Ring networks, which limitnetworks to a maximum of seven 'hops' from origin to finaldestination and require each device on the network to know theroute to every other device.andP;  Wellfleet's Extended Source Routing(ESR) scheme builds a routing table with route designators fromeach 'explorer' packet received.andP;  The hop count contained in apacket is reset by encapsulating the Token Ring data into anotherprotocol and sending it across the wide area network (WAN).andP;  Whenthe packet arrives at its destination and the data isunencapsulated, it appears to have seven hops remaining.andO;Wellfleet's scheme is compliant with IEEE standards and istherefore interoperable with other source-routing transparentbridges.andP;  ESR will be submitted to the IEEE's 802.1D committee forconsideration as an optional standard.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wellfleet Communications Inc. (Product development).andO;Topic:     New TechniqueLocal area networksToken ring networksRouting.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Wellfleet extended source routing. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>